title: Shirakawa-go Village
description: Shirakawa-go is a historic village located in Gifu Prefecture, Japan. It is famous for its traditional gassho-zukuri farmhouses, some of which are more than 250 years old. The village is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and offers visitors a glimpse into rural life in Japan.

title: Ouchi-juku Village
description: Ouchi-juku is a picturesque village located in Fukushima Prefecture, Japan. It was once a post town along the Aizu-Nishi Kaido trade route and is known for its well-preserved thatched-roof buildings. Visitors can experience the atmosphere of the Edo period while strolling through the village.

title: Shimoguri-no-sato Village
description: Shimoguri-no-sato is a charming village nestled in the mountains of Nagano Prefecture, Japan. It is known for its beautiful scenery, traditional thatched-roof houses, and hot springs. Visitors can relax in the onsens while enjoying the tranquil atmosphere of the village.

title: Tsumago-juku Village
description: Tsumago-juku is a historic post town located in Nagano Prefecture, Japan. It is part of the Nakasendo, a historic route that connected Kyoto and Edo during the Edo period. The village has preserved its traditional architecture and offers visitors a glimpse into Japan's past.

title: Narai-juku Village
description: Narai-juku is a historic post town located in Nagano Prefecture, Japan. It was once an important stop along the Nakasendo highway and is known for its well-preserved Edo-period buildings. Visitors can explore the town's quaint streets and learn about its rich history.
